        "Dental trauma or an accident might occur, and it can severely disrupt a person&#8217;s teeth functioning. Besides having a bad teeth appearance, it can also result in lower self-esteem. Moreover, it can also cause severe dental pain accompanied by other symptoms. A cosmetic dentist can recommend full mouth reconstruction to help restore oral health and [&hellip;]",
      author: "Procopio Towle Dental Office",
      content:
        '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental trauma or an accident might occur, and it can severely disrupt a person\'s teeth functioning. Besides having a bad teeth appearance, it can also result in lower self-esteem. Moreover, it can also cause severe dental pain accompanied by other symptoms. A cosmetic dentist can recommend full mouth reconstruction to help restore oral health and attain confidence.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You probably have significant teeth damage if you have experienced dental trauma. When damaged teeth are left untreated, they create further complications. You must be willing to visit the dentist for a quick restoration. Let\'s explore what full mouth reconstruction is and the steps involved in this procedure.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>What is Full Mouth Reconstruction (FMR)?&nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A cosmetic full mouth reconstruction is a procedure that aims at restoring a person\'s dental health. This holistic treatment is all you need for unhealthy gums, missing teeth, and other complications. FMR is an ideal treatment for people with multiple missing teeth, broken teeth, severe tooth decay, and large cavities. However, it\'s best to evaluate yourself if you are a candidate for this treatment. Usually, it is good to consider the following circumstances:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Severe Gum Disease</strong>. If you are suffering from advanced gum disease, it increases the chance of getting serious health complications. These include teeth loss, oral infections, systemic health conditions, etc. A cosmetic full mouth reconstruction will help ensure the health of your teeth and gums. Also, it will improve the appearance of your mouth.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Excessively Worn Teeth</strong>. Our teeth wear down with age, and this is entirely normal. However, excessively worn teeth can lead to pulp infection, a misaligned bite, and other serious issues. A full mouth rehabilitation may include root canals, crown placements, dental tooth extractions, and replacements.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Accident or Trauma</strong>. You might need a full mouth reconstruction if you have experienced an accident, trauma, or sports injury. Dental trauma can leave you with damage to your teeth, and a full mouth rehabilitation can correct your situation.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Chronic or Jaw Pain</strong>. This treatment might be best for you if you have certain types of chronic pain. You might be suffering from Temporomandibular disorders, have jaw soreness, or have pain in the muscles. Why not visit your dentist to elevate your state and say goodbye to these chronic pains?&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":5854,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/208a.jpg" alt="Procedural Steps Involved in a Cosmetic Full Mouth Reconstruction" class="wp-image-5854"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>How Long Will It Take for Restoration?&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The length of the procedure might take one entire month or even more. It depends on the specific needs of the patient. However, in most cases, a full mouth reconstruction usually requires several procedures to be carried out. So they might take a bit longer than other dental treatments.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Steps Involved in FMR:&nbsp;</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each patient\'s need is different. Some might need a full mouth reconstruction because of an accident or trauma. Others need it because of an underlying medical condition or otherwise. Some of the usual steps involved in this procedure include the following:&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Initial Consultation</strong>. At first, the patient has to undergo an initial consultation with a cosmetic dentist. The dentist will discuss the treatment\'s primary goals and other concerns here. Also, he would take the patient\'s entire medical history and resolve the patient\'s query.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Records and Impressions</strong>. At this step, the impressions of the patient\'s teeth are taken and recorded. Further, they are analyzed to create the treatment plan per the patient\'s oral health needs.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>3D Printing</strong>. The dentist will create a digital design and a 3D model of dental restorations here. The patient will also test the mockup restorations before final adjustments.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Treatment Plan</strong>. The dentist will make a treatment plan to facilitate the patient\'s oral health. The dentist will create a treatment plan using the patient\'s previous visual examination results. It can include procedures like corrective jaw surgery, removal of certain teeth, placing implants, root canal therapy, and so on.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Treatment</strong>. A full mouth reconstruction involves multiple sittings at the dentist and is carried out in different stages.&nbsp;</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Conclusion</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A full mouth reconstruction is one of the most complex procedures in modern dentistry. However, due to advanced techniques, the success rate is much higher. Knowing about a cosmetic full mouth reconstruction is essential to facilitate yourself and your significant others. It\'s always better to deal with an issue proactively and be well-informed on time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>,\u00a0to learn more about the Procedural Steps Involved in a Cosmetic Full Mouth Reconstruction.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Resource:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/what-is-cosmetic-dentistry/">What is Cosmetic Dentistry?</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
