  //     "Types of Dental implants offer an excellent way for smile restoration. It uses advanced technology where patients do not need to undergo painful tooth extraction. Recent\u202fstatistics\u202freveal that the adult population aged between 35-44 has at least one or more missing teeth. You might be lucky if you are over 40 and have all your teeth. [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Procopio Towle Dental Office",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Types of Dental implants offer an excellent way for smile restoration. It uses advanced technology where patients do not need to undergo painful tooth extraction. Recent\u202fstatistics\u202freveal that the adult population aged between 35-44 has at least one or more missing teeth. You might be lucky if you are over 40 and have all your teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might need a tooth extraction in the future if you have one or more missing teeth. However, with modern dental technology, there are numerous other ways to restore your dental smile. Dental implants are one of them and are gaining tremendous popularity worldwide.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are numerous types of dental implants, and most of them are either made of titanium or alloys. This metal is biocompatible with human bone structure and has a high specific strength. Continue reading to learn about the most common types of dental implants and some essential facts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":5682,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/715.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5682"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Type 1: Endosteal Implants</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Endosteal implants are the most typical type of implants that usually come in the shape of small screws. They are generally made of titanium and protrude through the patient\u2019s gum to hold the replacement tooth. Endosteal implants can be for one or multiple crowns. The support structure, such as a specialized cylinder or screw, is placed in the patient\u2019s jawbone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Afterward, it becomes incorporated within the implant\u2019s structure, providing outstanding durability. The patient must have the sufficient bone density to support these types of implants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Type 2: Subperiosteal Implants</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Subperiosteal implant placement is on or above the patient\u2019s jawbone. It\u2019s put under the gum so that it sticks to it for holding the implant. It is an excellent alternative to endosteal implants and has been in dental practice for many years.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These types of implants are mostly referred to when the patient doesn\u2019t have the sufficient bone density to support the implants. Or, if the patient cannot wear regular dentures, these implants could be the best option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Type 3: Zygomatic Implants</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zygomatic implants have a high success rate, just like traditional implants. So, their placement is in the cheekbone rather than the jawbone. It is a good option for patients who want dental implants but have severe bone loss in the upper jaw.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the treatment process is more complex than other dental implant types. Dentists only recommend zygomatic implants if the patient can\u2019t undergo other methods.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Important Facts About Dental Implants</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental implants are a great alternative to traditional dentures and bridgework. They might be the best option to restore your lost teeth. Therefore, knowing important facts about dental implants before undergoing the procedure is essential. It will help you understand their worth, and you can rely on the treatment confidently.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Dental implant surgery isn\u2019t complicated. Though it is invasive, it isn\u2019t dangerous.</li><li>Caring for implants is relatively easy. You need to maintain your oral hygiene to care for them appropriately.</li><li>Dental implants are highly durable and mimic natural teeth in strength and look.</li><li>The implants guard against bone loss and help preserve the jawbone.</li><li>Dental implants provide significant health benefits and boost the patient\u2019s confidence.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Conclusion</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Are you ready for your implant placement? Then, why not visit your dentist today and have all the procedures done? Dental implants will not improve your oral health functioning but also boost your self-confidence. By which you can easily smile in public without any fear or embarrassment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks to modern technology, which has made it easy to restore peoples\u2019 smiles. However, choosing the right type of implant is essential to have long-term benefits. Talk to your dentist and evaluate yourself to know which implant suits you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="tel:925-933-5677">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>,\u00a0to know more about dental implants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Resource:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/how-does-the-dental-implant-procedure-work/">How does the dental implant procedure work?</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
