  //     "Mobile dentistry is a recent trend, but according to experts\u2019 estimations, the\u202fmobile dental unit market\u202fhas the potential to reach millions in 2022. It brings dental services within reach of patients who cannot avail themselves otherwise. These patients mainly include senior adults who are either placed in hospitals and nursing homes or stay home and cannot [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Procopio Towle Dental Office",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mobile dentistry is a recent trend, but according to experts\u2019 estimations, the\u202fmobile dental unit market\u202fhas the potential to reach millions in 2022. It brings dental services within reach of patients who cannot avail themselves otherwise. These patients mainly include senior adults who are either placed in hospitals and nursing homes or stay home and cannot travel. Other patients include children or adults of low-income families or those who suffer from dental phobias.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The goal of mobile dentistry is to provide convenient access to various dental services and get rid of patient excuses. In a way, it also focuses on improving patients\u2019 life quality regardless of their proximity or accessibility. The benefits of mobile dentistry are numerous; however, this article will enlighten you with the top 5 benefits. So, let\u2019s discuss and get to know them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Keep Patients in Their Comfort Zone</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some patients do not like to visit the hospital due to several reasons. It might be because they feel frustrated with waiting for their turn or cannot travel. However, they need treatment on an immediate basis but cannot go out to see a dentist. A mobile dental unit can provide significant help in this regard. It keeps patients in their comfort zone, getting appropriate consultation and quality treatment for their problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":5543,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/351.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5543"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Offers Easy Access to Everyone</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mobile dentistry offers easy access to oral health care to all societal groups. Be it the elderly population, disadvantaged groups, marginalized communities, or otherwise, a mobile dental unit is easily accessible. It doesn\u2019t discriminate against people based on gender, age, status, religion, race, color, caste, creed, or otherwise. Rather, it treats everyone with dignity and respect and helps to resolve patients\u2019 issues quickly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Blessing To the Elderly</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mobile dentistry is a promising way to reach out to the elderly population. Studies reveal that many of the elderly population who lives in nursing homes need adequate oral health care. They feel deprived of one of their few remaining pleasures of life if not treated well on time. Oral conditions adversely impact seniors\u2019 quality of life, jeopardizing their nutritional status. Mobile dentistry uses technologically advanced equipment and provides restorative and preventive oral health services.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Provides Immediate Help</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes patients need immediate help and cannot visit the dental clinic. For instance, children cannot go out without parents who they might stick in their busy work schedules. Similarly, at times, there is a dental emergency, and the patient is alone at home and can\u2019t leave to avail of the treatment. In such a case, mobile dentistry is of valuable help. It provides immediate dental care at the doorstep, where patients feel receive quality treatment within the comfort of the mobile unit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Expands The Patient Base Exponentially</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mobile dentistry helps to boost dental practice. It expands the patient base exponentially and has low startup costs than a traditional clinic. A dentist can increase his efficiency with the help of modern dental care and advanced materials. Moreover, he can work on new cases to boost his dental experience while working within the community.\u202f\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Conclusion</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mobile dentistry focuses on the disadvantaged groups of society. It helps alleviate their problems instantly. Patients receive an efficient, accurate, and friendly quality of treatment from certified and trained medical staff. This way, they do not need to go out and wait for long hours to fix their dental problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead, they receive immediate help and feel relaxed after getting the treatment. If you are looking for a mobile dental clinic in your area, search on Google and get your work done in the best possible manner.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>\u00a0your Dentist in Walnut Creek, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>\u00a0to know more about the benefits of mobile dentistry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Resource:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/benefits-of-a-family-dentistry/">Benefits of A Family Dentistry</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em>\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
