  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We often do not visit the dentist regularly because dental anxiety or the problem is not as severe. However, if you know the importance of seeing a dental clinic with your whole family, you will not miss any appointments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The issues of toddlers, adults, and the elderly are different; therefore, a regular dental visit is necessary for each member. Regular visits help you identify your problem at the right time, including routine cleaning and fluoride varnish that helps achieve a bright smile. The cleaning also avoids any plaque accumulation in your teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Main advantages of regular visits to the clinic:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":5181,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/50-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5181"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>To save your natural teeth:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We often ignore the mild dental issues and only consider them when the situation is complex. The tooth decay in the back teeth is usually not noticeable due to the painless condition. And maybe the plaque is located at the backside or between the two teeth. It becomes severe when it transforms into cavities which can lead to tooth extraction in the future if not treated correctly and on time. So, visiting a dental clinic plays a massive role in saving your natural teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>To educate yourself on dental issues:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When we get a dental issue at the start, we begin to treat it at home according to our knowledge which is not helpful. All dental problems have different causes and treatments due to various reasons. Diagnosing and treating the exact problem can help you get prompt treatment with quick recovery and prevent damage to other healthy teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Much information about any dental problem is available on the internet, but it only lets us know about the cause and the treatment. Understanding the situation we face is possible only by regular dental visits for the whole family.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Prevent tooth damage in the future:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":5182,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/48.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5182"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Teeth problems only get severe when not treated on time due to lack of information and no visits to the clinic. We don\u2019t know when the problem has started in our teeth, and it starts spreading slowly with time. Regular visits to the clinic help identify the problem as soon as possible and treat it accordingly. In this way, there will be no severe conditions in the future, and you will enjoy a beautiful smile for your whole life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Conclusion:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are still doubting the importance of regular dental visits, look at all their benefits. It is best to know the problems early as prevention is always better than the cure. Regular visits provide the most significant advantage in enjoying your favorite food and having that beautiful smile. This increases self-esteem and boosts confidence. If you or your family members have not visited the clinic yet, book your appointment to save your teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>\u00a0today to know the importance of regular visits to your dentist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Resource:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/dental-anxiety/">Afraid to see your dentist?</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em>\u202f.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
