  //     "Invisalign is best to consider for people who have mild to moderate issues related to their bite. It works best for patients who want a comfortable straightening method to correct their crooked or misaligned teeth. Everyone cannot wear traditional braces or can bear the pain of exertion on teeth. In such cases, Invisalign aligners offer [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Invisalign is best to consider for people who have mild to moderate issues related to their bite. It works best for patients who want a comfortable straightening method to correct their crooked or misaligned teeth. Everyone cannot wear traditional braces or can bear the pain of exertion on teeth. In such cases, Invisalign aligners offer the best orthodontic treatment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Invisalign: A Quick Overview:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Invisalign is a thin clear aligner that is made from flexible thermoplastic material. It changes teeth positioning over time and treats issues of bite, teeth gap, crowded, or crooked teeth. Invisalign is an orthodontic treatment that helps straighten teeth with custom-made, clear braces.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Invisalign works quickly and ensures a comfortable experience for the patient. They feel comfortable wearing Invisalign aligners and don\u2019t have problems related to chewing. Invisalign offers a discreet and effective solution to treat less severe dental issues.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":5167,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/14.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5167"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>How To Know Whether You Need Invisalign Aligners?</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Recent statistics reveal that over 6 million people have chosen Invisalign over traditional braces for various reasons. Here are some key signs that indicate Invisalign is the right choice for you. Let\u2019s discuss them briefly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>You have had braces before.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have had braces before and are tired of wearing them any further, Invisalign is the right choice for you. As a teenager or adult, there are times when you begin to skimp on wearing the retainer for one reason or another.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this case, Invisalign is a suitable recommendation as it comes with a simple tune-up process where your teeth can quickly return to their previous state.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>You aren\u2019t happy with your smile.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You need Invisalign when you look in the mirror and don\u2019t feel good about your smile. Invisalign offers a virtually invisible way to treat your crooked teeth where you can smile with confidence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>You want teeth straightening without metal usage.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Metal braces restrict your eating habits and are quite painful compared to Invisalign. One might also experience excessive pain or bleeding while wearing braces. Braces need time to adjust, whereas Invisalign provides a quick method to straighten your teeth with a painless experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>You have a busy life.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you cannot afford to visit your dentist regularly due to a busy life, go for Invisalign. While traditional braces are time-consuming and involve frequent dental visits, Invisalign has a simple care procedure. You\u2019ll only need teeth cleanings twice a year with fewer dental check-ups.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>You have mild teeth problems.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Invisalign works best for mild to moderate teeth problems. If you can follow instructions and want a permanent solution for your teeth, consider choosing Invisalign.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>The Bottom Line:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Having crooked or misaligned teeth can be embarrassing, and one must strive to attain a healthy smile. Thanks to Invisalign aligners, which provide faster results to help relieve patients\u2019 confidence. Are you ready to take a step toward achieving a beautiful smile? Then, consult your dentist to avail of Invisalign. We hope that the given information will bring about a positive change in your life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>\u00a0today to learn more about Invisalign.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Resource:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/what-is-an-invisalign-treatment/">What Is An Invisalign Treatment?</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em>\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
