  //   excerpt:
  //     "Every medical or dental procedure has its advantages and disadvantages, even if it is extraordinarily safe. Though the all-on-4 dental implants have benefitted many people around the globe, it is, however, important to highlight the drawbacks or risks associated with these dental implants. Doing so will help you know whether it\u2019s the right fit for [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every medical or dental procedure has its advantages and disadvantages, even if it is extraordinarily safe. Though the all-on-4 dental implants have benefitted many people around the globe, it is, however, important to highlight the drawbacks or risks associated with these dental implants. Doing so will help you know whether it\u2019s the right fit for you or not. Read this article to learn the advantages and disadvantages of all-on-4 dental implants so that you can evaluate them as per your needs. So, let\u2019s begin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Advantages</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are numerous benefits of these dental implants. Here, we will only highlight 5 of them. These are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They improve patients\u2019 quality of life.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From comfortable chewing to stimulating healthy new bone tissues, the all-on-4 dental implants restore all your dental malfunction and will last a lifetime. They will quickly replace your missing or decayed teeth by offering a pleasant experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":5149,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/vigo-40.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5149"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They prevent bone deterioration.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These dental implants work in the same manner as natural teeth do, exert the same force against the jawbone, and preserve the jaw structure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They are fitted quickly and improve teeth appearance.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These implants are fitted within the same day, and this whole process is quickly done for the patient\u2019s benefit. The recovery is also quick, with immediate results.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They offer a secure and permanent solution.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The all-on-4 dental implants offer a permanent solution to your teeth and are surgically placed in your jawbone. They serve as roots of missing teeth, and if they are adequately cared for, they can last throughout your lifetime.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They are more convenient to use as compared to dentures.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental implants are easier to maintain as compared to dentures. You\u2019ll need fewer dental visits with these, and their adjustment is relatively easy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Disadvantages</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Though the all-on-4 dental implants have several benefits, they also have some drawbacks. Some of them are listed below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>The patient will need to stick to a liquid diet first.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After the placement of these dental implants, the patient will need to stick to a liquid diet for about two weeks. Afterward, they are recommended to stay on a semi-liquid diet for about six months so that the implant can adequately fuse with the bone tissue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":5150,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/vigo-42.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-5150"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>It causes tender gums during the healing process.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The gums become tender during the healing process and might lead to periodontics. So, the person has to take special care of his diet for a certain period to minimize these effects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>They are costly for many.</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Though dental implants are less costly than individual tooth treatments, they are still expensive for many. The range mainly lies between 2,800-6,000 U.S. dollars, respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Final Thoughts</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is no doubt that all-on-4 dental implants have gained significant prominence worldwide and have benefitted many. But it is equally important to know whether it\u2019s right for you or not. Discuss with your dentist in this regard to get the best treatment for yourself.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>&nbsp;Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle&nbsp;your Walnut Creek Dentist, DDS at&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>,&nbsp;and learn more about the All-on-4 Dental Implants.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Resource:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><a href="https://pwdds.com/procedure-for-all-on-4-dental-implants/">The Procedure for All-on-4 Dental Implants</a></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*Neither this nor any other content in this media is meant to prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fWe\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
