  //     "Teeth loss is a natural process. After all, they go through a lot every day. Procedure for All-on-4 dental implants is a dental solution that\u202fcan restore your\u202fsmile if you have lost\u202fall upper or lower teeth. Compared to removable dentures, dentures anchored with four dental implants appear, feel, and work exactly like natural healthy teeth. They [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Teeth loss is a natural process. After all, they go through a lot every day. Procedure for All-on-4 dental implants is a dental solution that\u202fcan restore your\u202fsmile if you have lost\u202fall upper or lower teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Compared to removable dentures, dentures anchored with four dental implants appear, feel, and work exactly like natural healthy teeth. They are long-lasting, durable, and allow you to do your day-to-day activities without worrying about making compromises. In this article, we explain the procedure for all-on-4 dental implants to help you understand and prepare for it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Consultation and diagnosis</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first step in getting all-on-four implants is to book an appointment\u202fwith an implant dentist so that they can examine your situation. A dental implant consultation will include an examination of your mouth, including tests and scans. Your implant dentist will review your medical history, current medicines, and any ongoing\u202fhealth issues to evaluate if you are a good candidate for oral surgery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your dentist will give you a treatment plan at the end of your consultation. If you opt to proceed\u202fwith advised\u202ftreatment, you will have to schedule your implant surgery on another\u202fday. A pre-op consultation can also happen in some situations to discuss dental sedation methods, preparation, and review of any necessary medications.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Implant Placement</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the day of your appointment, it will be better to wear comfortable clothing and closed-toed shoes. Your implant dentist will use dental sedation to get you ready for the surgery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":4849,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/vigora-14.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4849"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your dentist will begin the process of removing any remaining teeth from your jaw. A minor incision in your gums will be made to access the jawbone and create a suitable socket for implant placement.\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He will join an abutment or connector to the implant screw in the jawbone. Sometimes, your dentist may insert part of the implant\'s bone material and stitch it into place around the abutment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The top and lower arch will have four dental implants. While the implant sites are healing, these implants will be responsible for holding a temporary denture in place.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Healing</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Following the placement of your dental implants, the final step is to allow them to recover correctly. You may notice some little discomfort and swelling following your operation. Most dental implant patients report mild postoperative pain, easily handled with over-the-counter painkillers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It takes a 3\u20136-month process called osseointegration for your dental implants to heal properly. After this period, new bone development surrounding the implant bonds it. You must avoid putting too much pressure on your freshly implanted teeth. Therefore, your dentist may recommend a soft food diet. If you apply too much force to your implants too early, they may fall loose or heal incorrectly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Final Thoughts</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The procedure for all-on-4 dental implants requires patience and perseverance but offers a lifelong result. Finding a dentist that utilizes items with a high reputation is one of the most essential things before getting all-on-4 dental implants. Make sure your implants are made of high-quality materials to meet rigorous safety standards. We\'re here to help you choose the ideal implant system for your needs and give you a smile you\'ll be proud to show off. Learn about All-on-4 dental implants by contacting us now.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a> Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle</em> your Walnut Creek Dentist, DDS at\u00a0\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>,<em> and learn more about the procedure for All-on-4 Dental Implants.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Resource:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><a href="https://pwdds.com/how-does-the-dental-implant-procedure-work/">How does the dental implant procedure work?</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>This media/content or any other on this website does not prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fTherefore, we\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em>\u202f</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
