  //     "Dental crowns can be used to restore a badly damaged tooth, or to form a tooth to fit the rest of your teeth. Getting a dental crown is simple and affordable. I pray you never need a crown. But not everyone is so lucky. You need not be concerned about dental crowns because they are [&hellip;]",
  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental crowns can be used to restore a badly damaged tooth, or to form a tooth to fit the rest of your teeth. Getting a dental crown is simple and affordable. I pray you never need a crown. But not everyone is so lucky. You need not be concerned about dental crowns because they are often used nowadays. If you keep your teeth clean, your crowns should last a long time. Because benefits of dental crowns is that they are custom-made to match your teeth, your friends and family may not know you have one.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Types of Dental Crowns:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A crown is a type of cap that covers a decaying tooth. Porcelain and metal are only a couple of examples of materials. A front tooth crown that matches the rest of your teeth, or a molar crown that only shows when you yawn, are both options to consider.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When choosing a crown, take the following points in mind:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The price of a crown,</li><li>Because of its power,</li><li>Furthermore, it has a long shelf life.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Crowns made up of:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your natural teeth are in good condition and do not detract from your appearance, they may be crucial to you. A dentist can assist you in evaluating all your alternatives and selecting the most appropriate one for you. Mouth crowns are available in a variety of shapes and sizes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":4637,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/dental-8.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4637"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental crowns are made of several materials, including:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>porcelain</li><li>ceramic</li><li>zirconia</li><li>Metal</li><li>composites made of resin</li><li>a mix of several things</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Benefits of Dental Crowns</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>Improved chewing and eating ability</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a tooth is knocked out or injured, it can have an impact on your ability to eat and chew. In recent years, advancements in dental technology have improved the materials used to construct dental crowns, allowing you to consume your favorite meals with fewer restrictions than ever before.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>    </strong> 2<strong>. Protection</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A dental crown is a cap or cover placed over a damaged tooth or implant to protect it from further damage. It fits nicely over the top and is securely fastened. A dental crown fitted on a tooth that has been injured in any way will protect it against infection in the future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>     3<strong>. Flexibility</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dental crowns can be used to treat a wide variety of dental issues, depending on your specific scenario. Using a crown to support a dental bridge or dental implants, you can restore your smile if you have a missing tooth that cannot be preserved. After a root canal procedure, a dental crown can be utilized to restore stability to the tooth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Consideration</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Porcelain fused to a metal crown, rather than an all-porcelain crown, is an example of this type of crown. When selecting a crown material, your dentist will consider the following factors:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Understanding your dental health</li><li>Some of your teeth are visible when you grin.</li><li>The link between the gums and the rest of the body</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/contact">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>\u00a0today to learn more about Dental Crowns.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Resource:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>O<a href="https://pwdds.com/orthodontic-treatments/">rthodontic Treatments</a><a href="https://pwdds.com/author/emily-brownvigorant-com/"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>*Neither this nor any other content in this media is meant to prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fWe\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
