  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Orthodontic Treatments are dental procedures for straightening and moving to enhance teeth\'s appearance. They are also used to correct bite problems with the help of braces. These treatments are also helpful in improving oral health. These treatments are performed by specialists known as orthodontists. Orthodontists treat kids, teenagers, and adult individuals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why Might We Need Orthodontic Treatment?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>A Tooth That Is Crooked Or Sticks Out</li><li>The Upper And Lower Jaws Meet At The Wrong Angle When Closed</li><li>Badly Aligned Jaws</li><li>Gaps Are Present Between The Teeth</li><li>Problems That Occur During Speaking, Chewing And Biting</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What To Expect From An Orthodontic Treatment?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Orthodontics will discuss and examine your mouth and teeth. The specialist will do your x-ray or make plaster models of your teeth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"left","id":3434,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignleft size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/braces.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-3434"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The orthodontics will talk about the treatment options. Treatments include braces to straighten the teeth, especially the crooked ones. It helps to correct the bite problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Different types of braces are also available, including metal ones. Other kinds of braces include tooth-colored braces, braces worn on the inside surface of the teeth, and removable aligners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the start, the braces may cause discomfort, but with time they will dissolve. If the discomfort does not disappear, talk to your doctor about it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How Long Do These Treatments Take?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Orthodontic Treatment may take up to two years, and you must see the doctor regularly during this period. So many people will have to wear a specific device for some time. Some people must wear braces or some device for a lifetime. Over time, the crooked teeth come back to their original position. For some people, the doctor advises using it only at night.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cost Of Orthodontic Treatment</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The cost of orthodontic treatment depends on the problematic teeth. If the problem is severe, then the cost increases automatically. Discuss the prices with the doctor. The cost must include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Consulting Fees</li><li>Pre-treatment Advice</li><li>Use of Appliance Used In Orthodontic Treatment</li><li>Reviews of Doctor After Treatment</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some health insurances also cover orthodontic treatments. You have to check your insurance company before the treatment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pros and Cons of Orthodontic Treatment</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"align":"right","id":3435,"sizeSlug":"full","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-full"><img src="https://pwdds.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/orthodontic-treatment.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-3435"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Orthodontic Treatment helps improve the look and appearance of your teeth and the bite. It can also help in improving the problems related to speech and breath. If you have straight teeth, you will have a lower risk of a bad bite and improvement of oral health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand, orthodontic treatments are expensive and take a very long time. It will take some time to adjust to wearing braces and how to take care of them. Orthodontic treatment is not recommended if you have unhealthy jaws and teeth. If you wear braces, it is essentially brushing your teeth properly and avoiding unhealthy food such as sugars and soft drinks. Otherwise, it may lead to tooth decay.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="tel:925-933-5677">Contact</a>\u00a0your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at\u00a0<a href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a>\u00a0today to learn more about Dental Inlays and Onlays.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Resource:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/invisalign-step-by-step-procedure/">Invisalign Step by Step Procedure</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>*Neither this nor any other content in this media is meant to prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.\u202fWe\u202fhighly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
