  //   author: "Dr. Tiziana Procopio",
  //   content:
  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are thinking of whitening your teeth, you should do some research first. Not everyone can opt for teeth whitening. Teeth Whitening works best for yellow teeth, but if the teeth are turned grey or black, teeth whitening will not work. Similarly, some cases are strictly forbidden for teeth whitening. Here we are going into the details:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="causes-for-tooth-decay">Causes For Tooth Decay</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All of us may face some discoloration at one point in our life. Several reasons cause this discoloration. Many drinks such as coffee and hot drink cause these stains. Similarly, tobacco also leaves yellow marks on the teeth. Experiencing an oral injury can cause stains on the teeth. Other than that, certain antibiotics also play a role in teeth yellowing. The outer layer of the teeth, called the enamel, also becomes weak with time and eventually wears off, and the inner layer is exposed, which is yellow. So, teeth Whitening can restore the original color of your teeth, and you can smile with confidence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="1-people-suitable-for-teeth-whitening">1. People Suitable For Teeth Whitening</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People who have healthy teeth are eligible for professional teeth whitening. If the candidate has no history of dental treatments like filling or restorations, they become perfect for teeth whitening. So, the dentist will go into the details to know if you can go for this treatment or not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="2-people-who-are-not-suitable-for-teeth-whitening">2. People Who Are Not Suitable For Teeth Whitening</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Teeth Whitening is not ideal for everyone. It is not an efficient way to do treatment without doing a little research on the patient. Candidates who are not appropriate for teeth whitening are given below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Children Under 16 Years Old</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The dentist does not recommend kids who are below 16 teeth whitening. This is the pulp of the teeth, which is bigger than the adults. Teeth Whitening can cause sensitivity and irritation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Pregnant And Lactating Females</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pregnant and lactating women are not suitable for teeth whitening because it may be dangerous for their health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Previous Dental Treatments</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If a candidate has a history of Root Canal Treatments, crowns, and bridges, the dentist will not suggest teeth whitening. The reason is that the restoration will not respond to bleaching treatments, and the process will be tiring. Similarly, if a candidate has dental diseases like broken teeth, tooth decay, and cavities whitening process would not be appropriate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>People Who Have Sensitive Teeth</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People who have sensitivity issues are not the right choice for teeth whitening. This is because sensitive teeth may be allergic to peroxides used in teeth whitening.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, the bottom line is before considering Teeth Whitening consult your doctor. He will check your oral hygiene to know if you can go for the treatment or not. Best of luck!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="tel:925-933-5677">Contact</a> your dentist in Walnut Creek, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at <a title="Procopio Dental Office" href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Dental Office</a> today to schedule your visit!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="resource">Resource</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/the-important-of-regular-teeth-cleaning/" title="The Importance of Regular Teeth Cleaning">The Importance of Regular Teeth Cleaning</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>*Neither this nor any other content in this media is meant to prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure. We highly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
