  //     '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your dentist or dental hygienist will discuss treatment options for decay or other oral issues. so, what kind of coverage will your tooth get following the repair? Although "fillings" are a frequent term for tooth repair, there are various options. Inlays include inlays, onlays, fillings. What distinguishes an inlay from a crown? What is a dental onlay? What if I\'ve had a dental injury? Let us investigate the benefits of dental inlays over and if one needs it or not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="so-what-s-the-point">So, what\'s the point?</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:group -->\n<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After reading this, you might be tempted to acquire one, In minor tooth decay, fractures, and other dental disorders. In some circumstances, dental repairs are required.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="an-inlay">An Inlay</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Inlays and onlays can treat small cracks and break in teeth. Dental caries on the "cusps" or outside borders are repaired with this material. Cavities rarely impact the rest of the tooth.<br><br>An inlay is a simple and painless surgery. It involves numbing the area and drilling out the decayed tooth. A dental lab will make a replica of your tooth after cleaning its crevices. Porcelain or composite resins inlays are commonly used for this purpose.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="an-onlay"><br>An Onlay</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An onlay can repair a tooth that has been chipped or broken on the cusp. An inlay fills the tooth\'s grooves, whereas an onlay covers its edges. Oral inlays and onlays are similar to dental onlays. A mild local anesthetic will be used to perform the procedure. Then a temporary dental onlay will cover the decayed or broken tooth. Your dentist will take an impression and send it to the lab. And will put the permanent onlay.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="fillings">Fillings</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Is it filled? Most individuals have heard of and possibly used it. Fillings restore a small piece of your tooth after your dentist has cleaned out a cavity. They come in metal, glass, and acrylic resin. But conventional fillings have drawbacks. An inlay or onlay can strengthen teeth by 75 % and last twenty to thirty years</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Minor cavities can be filled for less than a crown, significant damage can be repaired with inlays and outlays. As a compromise between fillings and crowns, consider inlays. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="why-choose-an-inlay-or-an-onlay">Why Choose an Inlay or an Onlay?</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even with adequate oral hygiene and regular dental visits, harm can occur. An inlay is recommended if:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Non-cusp tooth injuries</li><li>Large dental fillings may undermiine the remaining structure.</li><li>Too much tooth material cannot be removed due tothe damage.</li><li>Inlay post-op care</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="final-thoughts">Final Thoughts</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An inlay surgery\'s long-term outcome depends on these 48 hours. Do not eat items that are sticky or hard. Your tongue only requires a few days of mild feeding. You may feel numb or in discomfort for a few days after surgery. Afterward, return to your regular oral hygiene routine!<br><br>With inlays, onlays, and fillings, you should discuss your options with your dentist. An inlay may be the best solution for you due to the materials\' durability.<br><br>It doesn\'t matter what you or your dentist think about it. Mouthwash and twice-daily brushing are the best ways to keep bacteria out. Regular dentist appointments will help you avoid dental problems. I should help you prevent cavities and reduce future surgery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="tel:925-933-5677">Contact</a> your Walnut Creek Dentist, Dr. Tiziana Procopio Towle, DDS at <a title="Procopio Towle Dental Office" href="https://pwdds.com/">Procopio Towle Dental Office</a> today to learn more about Dental Inlays and Onlays.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5 id="resource">Resource</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href="https://pwdds.com/dental-fillings-procedures-in-walnut-creek/" title="Dental Fillings">Dental Fillings</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>*Neither this nor any other content in this media is meant to prescribe, recommend, or prevent any treatment or procedure.&nbsp;We&nbsp;highly recommend that you get the advice of a qualified dentist or other medical practitioners regarding your specific dental condition</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',
