  //     'To Our Valued Patients:\n\nWe trust this message finds you and your families in good health and positive spirits given the unprecedented circumstances we live in. It has been three months since we re-opened our office and we could not be more excited to finally see most of you again.\u00a0 We would like to extend our sincere gratitude to all of you who have visited our practice during this period \u2013 your patience and understanding have made re-opening our office a little easier.\n\nDespite the challenges we have faced and will continue to face, our practice has grown slightly as new patients decide they would like to receive the type of dental care our office provides. In order to embrace this situation and continue providing you with the best standard of care, we have welcomed to our dental team:\n<p style="text-align: center;">Dr. Jing Ye (\u201cDr. Jing\u201d)\u00a0 who see patients on Mondays and started July 6, 2020</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Dr. Garik Oganesian (\u201cDr. O\u201d) who see patients on Wednesdays and selected Saturdays and started\u00a0 July 17, 2020.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Dr. Joyce Chi is still with our team and works on Thursdays and continues to be our expert in making CEREC Crowns (same day crowns) and is our Invisalign Provider.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://pwdds.com/meet-our-dentists-staffs/">Click here to get to know our Dentists</a></p>\nAs many of you are working remotely from home, adjusting to distance learning school schedules, getting ready for cooler weather, making upcoming holiday plans and more, you may not be thinking about your available or unused dental insurance benefits.\u00a0 Whether you have insurance benefits remaining or if you have funds set aside in a flexible spending account (FSA) or healthcare saving account (HSA), now might be a good time to schedule treatment so your patient portion payment amounts can be applied to this year\u2019s deductions. Please check that you have used all available benefits to complete any outstanding treatment or for your all-important preventive dental hygiene appointment (\u201ccheckup and cleaning\u201d). Most plans do not allow rollover unused dollars to the next benefit year and have a <strong><em>\u201cUse \u2018Em or Lose \u2018Em!\u201d</em></strong> approach.\n\nPlease call us today to schedule your appointment as we find that the upcoming holiday season is one of our busiest periods. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact our office.\n\nThank you,\nDr. Tiziana Procopio Towle',
